This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on April 14, 2011. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authority to the Secretary of Defense under sections 315 and 325 of Title 32 of the United States Code. Specifically, it grants the Secretary of Defense the power to allow commissioned officers of the Regular Army or Regular Air Force to accept commissions in the Army National Guard or Air National Guard without losing their rank or regular appointment. It also authorizes the service of National Guard officers on active duty without relieving them from duty in their respective National Guard units. This memorandum supersedes a previous delegation of functions and authority made in 2004. The Secretary of Defense is further directed to arrange for the necessary funding, establish regulations, and publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.